## Project Overview
Viper Hunt is a cyberpunk-themed browser-based arcade snake game where players control a Hunter entity navigating a grid matrix to capture criminal targets (or treasure vault loot) while avoiding self-collision, boundary hits, and roaming boss hazards.

## Tech Stack
- **Runtime:** Browser ES6+ (Native Vanilla JavaScript, no framework dependencies)
- **Rendering:** HTML5 Canvas 2D API with glowing vector rendering & particle FX
- **Styling:** Modular CSS3 with responsive mobile scaling, flexbox/grid, dynamic viewport overlays
- **Cloud Database:** Firebase Firestore (dynamic CDN import with local storage fallback)
- **Testing:** Node.js native test runner (`node --test tests/*.test.js`)
- **Data Source:** Remote Google Sheets CSV API with local JSON fallback (`data/fallback_registry.json`)

## Folder Structure
```
viper-hunt/
├── index.html                   # Game HTML shell, mode overlay, start/game-over screens, virtual D-Pad
├── main.js                      # Core entry point, mode selection, Firebase init, UI event wiring
├── style.css                    # Cyberpunk design system, glowing UI, responsive overlays, mobile D-Pad
├── init-db.js                   # Firestore initial database seed script
├── firebase-config.js           # Live Firebase configuration parameters
├── firebase-config.example.js   # Example configuration template
├── assets/                      # Graphic assets (avatars, icons, audio)
├── data/                        # Local fallback data (fallback_registry.json)
├── models/                      # Domain entities (CriminalRecord, HunterEntity)
├── services/                    # Game engine services
│   ├── CollisionDetector.js     # Grid boundary, self, and boss collision detection
│   ├── FirebaseService.js       # Firestore cloud sync & local storage persistence
│   ├── GameLoop.js              # Fixed delta requestAnimationFrame loop orchestrator
│   ├── GridState.js             # Spatial grid matrix, hunter segments, targets, boss position
│   ├── InputHandler.js          # WASD / Arrow key queueing & Virtual D-Pad touch controls
│   ├── LevelManager.js          # Target spawning, level progression, boss activation, recentering
│   ├── RegistryService.js       # Google Sheets CSV fetcher, XSS sanitizer, play mode provider
│   ├── Renderer.js              # Canvas 2D renderer, cyberpunk glow FX, particle explosions, loot shapes
│   ├── ScoreManager.js          # Level & session score calculators with time bonuses
│   └── TargetManager.js         # Random unoccupied grid cell target spawner
├── tests/                       # Unit & integration test suites
└── docs/                        # Project documentation (requirements, user stories, architecture, tasks)
```

## Components and Responsibilities
- **RegistryService** — Fetches CSV target data or fallback JSON; manages play mode definitions (`mode1` Viper Bounty Hunter, `mode2` Treasure Vault).
- **FirebaseService** — Cloud persistence for high scores and player profiles with fallback to `localStorage`.
- **GameLoop** — `requestAnimationFrame` loop driver, tick timing, game state orchestrator.
- **InputHandler** — Captures keyboard (WASD/Arrows) and touch D-Pad inputs; enforces reversal constraints & input queueing.
- **GridState** — Owns grid bounds, hunter coordinates, active targets, play mode state, and boss position.
- **CollisionDetector** — Pure spatial collision logic for walls, self-body, and roaming Big Boss figures.
- **LevelManager** — Manages level progression, hunter recentering, level target pools, and Big Boss hazard spawning.
- **TargetManager** — Selects random unoccupied grid coordinates for targets.
- **ScoreManager** — Computes capture values, level time bonuses, and session score totals.
- **Renderer** — Canvas 2D graphics engine rendering cyberpunk grid, hunter, targets, loot shapes, boss hazards, and particle FX.

## Key ADRs
- **ADR-001:** Remote Google Sheets CSV API with mandatory 5s timeout fallback to local `fallback_registry.json`.
- **ADR-002:** HTML5 Canvas 2D native renderer for optimal browser frame rates without heavy engine overhead.
- **ADR-003:** Firebase Firestore dynamic SDK loading with seamless degradation to `localStorage`.
- **ADR-004:** Responsive Mobile D-Pad Touch Controls overlay for universal device support.
- **ADR-005:** Dual Play Modes (`mode1`: Viper Bounty Hunter, `mode2`: Treasure Vault with distinct visual loot shapes).
- **ADR-006:** Cyberpunk visual theme featuring glowing vector canvas renderers and particle explosion FX.
- **ADR-007:** Roaming Criminal Big Boss figure hazard active on level progression.

## Do Not
- Do not add heavy third-party UI/game frameworks (e.g. Phaser, React) — maintain lightweight native ES6 architecture.
- Do not bypass `RegistryService` XSS sanitization when parsing remote payload fields.
- Do not hardcode pixel offsets without taking cell size and responsive scaling into account.
- Do not commit production Firebase keys or live credentials to `.env` or version control.
